# AdSense Consent Loading Rule

For ALL HTML files in this repository, you MUST wrap the AdSense script in a consent-gated function.
NEVER load the Google AdSense script automatically on initial page load.

Always implement this logic in the `<script>` section:

```javascript
// OpsCode Standard: Consent-Gated Ad Loading
function loadAdSense() {
    const script = document.createElement('script');
    script.src = "https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js?client=ca-pub-5449371042798610";
    script.async = true;
    script.crossOrigin = "anonymous";
    document.head.appendChild(script);
    console.log("SilenVault Ops: AdSense Initialized.");
}

function acceptCookies() {
    document.getElementById('cmp-banner').style.display = 'none';
    localStorage.setItem('sv_cookie_consent', 'true');
    loadAdSense(); // Only load ads NOW
}

function dismissCmp() {
    document.getElementById('cmp-banner').style.display = 'none';
}

// On page load, check if already accepted
if(localStorage.getItem('sv_cookie_consent') === 'true') {
    document.getElementById('cmp-banner').style.display = 'none';
    loadAdSense();
}
```

Make sure the CMP Banner (`#cmp-banner`) HTML always utilizes:
`<button onclick="dismissCmp()">Decline</button>`
`<button onclick="acceptCookies()">Accept</button>`
